text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Linguistic Discrimination during COVID-19 times%0a:Author: BrandonW%0a:Section: C%0a:Completed: 24.04.2021 - 20:59%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210505-022138-731940#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 19:21-] || TA_lili marked as complete%0a#foxend 210505-022138-731940#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome examples of language discrimination due to COVID-19%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn China, people listen for accents/dialects that distinctly come from Hubei Province, which is where COVID-19 outbreak started, and will shun these type of people. Examples include avoided these people on public transportation or denying them entry to public spaces or restaurants.%0a%0aIn Europe, Italy is one of the hotspots for the virus. Some Italians that have traveled abroad have been discriminated against for speaking their native language. An example is a man from Italy who traveled to Slovenia who got beat and robbed and called "Italiano coronoavirus" after people in Slovenia heard him speaking Italian.%0a%0aSource: https://undark.org/2020/05/05/covid-19-language-discrimination/%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_lili:)
